position description
box is looking for a lead interaction designer to craft exceptional digital experience design for the in-house creative team at box we're looking for a great talent and great partner that will take point on understanding customer need and behavior and using insight to craft experience that work and delight
please note this is a marketing and creative role not a product development role
at box designer work cross-functionally to shape and steer how our brand interface with the world as part of our in-house creative lab the interaction design lead work closely with writer visual designer content strategist data scientist and campaign manager to bring user-centric thinking and digital performance orientation into digital marketing program specifically the interaction design lead is responsible for crafting insights-driven persona define experience flow across temporal experience and lead out the creation of wireframes and similar artifact to drive a comprehensive view of the creative program as program reach certain checkpoint the interaction designer take lead on usability testing and partner closely with the marketing operation team to ensure the learning agenda carry into the metric within the marketing dashboard
the optimal candidate will be the voice of the customer in the experience while continuously championing the brand in the engagement you should be able to cogently think through the modern requirement of social engagement distributed application and content development and using marketing a a service rather than a bland sale tactic
